  "narration": "Niko shoves the cafeteria doors open with his shoulder and the smell hits first — canned corn, bleach, and something underneath both that nobody wants to name. The storage room in the back has eight cases of canned food left. Jules was right about the count. Niko grabs two cases and stacks them by the door.\n\nFedor finds the nurse's office locked. He puts his boot through the frosted glass window beside the door, reaches through, and turns the handle from inside. The office is small — an exam table with paper on it, a cabinet with bandages and ibuprofen, and a locked metal box bolted to the wall that probably has the real medicine. There is a sleeping bag on the floor behind the exam table. It is zipped shut and it is moving. Something inside is breathing fast and wet. A sneaker sticks out from the bottom — a kid's sneaker, red Converse, size seven.\n\nJules appears in the doorway behind Fedor. Her face goes white. Jules whispers, \"Don't open that. Please. Just — don't.\" Her hand is on the kitchen knife in her belt and her eyes are wet and she is looking at the sleeping bag like it is the only thing in the world.\n\nOutside, glass breaks. Two streets away, then one. The shuffling sound is getting louder and it is not one pair of feet anymore. The fluorescent light above the nurse's office door pops and dies. In the hallway, the emergency exit sign glows red and something hits the school's front door hard enough to rattle the frame.",
